  "local_port": 47812,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can your remove white underarm stains from shirts?",
  "response": "To remove white underarm stains from shirts, you can try the following methods:\n\n### Method 1: Using Vinegar and Water\n1. **Mix a Solution**: Combine equal parts of white vinegar and water in a bowl.\n2. **Apply the Solution**: Use a cloth or sponge to apply the solution directly to the stain. Make sure the stain is completely saturated.\n3. **Let it Sit**: Allow the solution to sit on the stain for at least 30 minutes.\n4. **Scrub Gently**: Use a soft brush or cloth to gently scrub the stain.\n5. **Wash the Shirt**: Launder the shirt as usual, following the care label instructions.\n\n### Method 2: Using Baking Soda and Hydrogen Peroxide\n1. **Make a Paste**: Mix baking soda and hydrogen peroxide to form a paste.\n2. **Apply the Paste**: Spread the paste over the stain and let it sit for an hour.\n3. **Scrub the Stain**: Gently scrub the stained area with a soft brush.\n4. **Rinse and Wash**: Rinse the shirt thoroughly and then wash it as usual.\n\n### Method 3: Using Lemon Juice\n1. **Apply Lemon Juice**: Squeeze fresh lemon juice directly onto the stain.\n2. **Let it Sit**: Allow the lemon juice to sit on the stain for about 10-15 minutes.\n3. **Rinse and Wash**: Rinse the shirt with cold water and then launder it as usual.\n\n### Method 4: Using Aspirin\n1. **Crush Aspirin**: Crush 2-3 aspirin tablets and mix with a small amount of warm water to make a paste.\n2. **Apply the Paste**: Spread the paste over the stain and let it sit for about 1-2 hours.\n3. **Rinse and Wash**: Rinse the shirt and then launder it as usual.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Pre-Treat Stains**: Always pre-treat stains before washing to improve the chances of removal.\n- **Avoid Heat**: Do not use hot water or heat to dry the shirt until the stain is completely gone, as heat can set the stain.\n- **Test a Small Area**: Before applying any stain removal solution, test it on a small, inconspicuous area of the shirt to ensure it doesn\u2019t damage the fabric.\n\nBy following these methods, you should be able to effectively remove white underarm stains from your shirts.",
